content.detailedDescription: I was sitting out at a bonfire in middletown watching the starts and talking to my family, this would make the second day we saw a weird object in the sky. we were just sitting there talking then suddenly a orange fireball appeared to be falling to earth it was quite big and bright then as the object proceeded to fall it turned into 4 objects right before our eyes. it did not seem to be a meteor because the rate at which these "things" were falling/traveling. i ran down the alley to get a better view of these things falling. it took me a while to get down there yet these things were still in the sky. my boyfirend ran ahead of me and said the object traveled to the west and finally fell out of eyesight. like i stated earlier this is the second night we have seen strange things in sky. after this experience we left to go how about 2 hours later. on our way home i seen 2 orange lights similar to the ones we saw fall only these 2 were traveling toward each other then got smaller and smaller out of view as to travel away.
content.summary: Fireball like object falls from the sky the breaks into 4 fireballs

content.detailedDescription:
Location: vienna, austria over josefsplatz, date: 27/09/2013 (9/27/2013), time: approx. 21:25-22:45  
looking out the north-facing windows of a building (the observable sky being only a small area over a courtyard).
six individuals witnessed the lights.  first one cluster of lights appeared from the north, traveling in a south/southeast direction, and was followed by 4 more clusters (5 in all).  they moved slowly and in a straight line.  there were virtually no clouds. the lights were observed until they disappeared over the top of our building, directly overhead.  they took approx. 2-3 minutes to pass over.  several minutes later, clouds had started to drift in and a large beam of light appeared, directly perpendicular to the direction the lights had been traveling, reflecting off the clouds.  the beam (possible a searchlight?) remained for approx. 10 minutes.
content.summary: 5 clusters of lights, greenish-white to orange in color, traveling slowly in a straight line in a s/se direction.

content.altitude: 500 Feet or Less, Over 500 Feet (under cloudcover)
content.detailedDescription: I was heading down buck rub from spring run rd. to deer run dr with my wife. while driving through the neighborhood, a bright orange and red object appeared over the trees in front of us at first i thought to myself, it's just airplane. that's when i realized it was quite a bit bigger and brighter than any airplane i've ever seen. also the fact that airplane headlights don't encompass the entire craft and the distinct absence of  the hallmark blinking airplane light lead me to believe that it was something neither i or my wife could explain. i mean the thing made no sound and it most certainly didn't look like any plane ive seen, experimental or otherwise. we kinda followed it as it moved horizontal across the sky but lost it behind more trees. it seemed to pulsate a kind of redish color in the middle of the orange glow. it also mover relatively fast, a little faster and lower than a commercial airplane but slower than a jet. my wife said she saw it dip down in quick increments, but i couldn't tell as i was trying not to hit people's mail boxes.
content.summary: Bright redish orange craft flew overhead while driving through the neighborhood.

content.detailedDescription: Sat. morning 09/28/2013 at exactly 5am in long beach ca was heading out to store noticed 3 lighter colored circles looked like balloons or birds in formation. noticed dull surfaced very dark ...Cast against dark blue sky then realized it was a triangle ufo. no sound lights were not lit like most sightings...No light source in the middle....It followed a direct path then shifted direction saw side profile ...Which was pretty flat..Then just disappeared. 1 other witness who saw exact same thing with me.
content.summary: Translucent triangle no lights flashing no sound followed path changed direction disappeared

content.detailedDescription: Me and three of my friends were driving to the mall as we were arriving we saw what we could only describe as a large misshapen piece of the sky moving in a straight path there were about 65 star like lights glowing and twinkling and the majority were very close together then there were about ten in various locations following the same path almost as would be the flight pattern of migrating birds trying to catch up to the flock we observed this for 5-6 min around 8 pm 9/28/2013 we were all very shaken up and dumbfounded as we had never seen anything like that and any guess as to what it could be was illogical we lost sight of the object as it got too far away it continued at the same speed the whole time and remained on a straight course.
content.summary: Looked like a very large piece of the night sky

content.detailedDescription: For more than two months i have wittnenesed what looked like a star but at a lower level than the normal seen stars on the horizon a bright star above the white sands missle range an below or levevel with the opposeing mountain range behind it to the sw. it has flashing changeing color pattern like christmjas tree lights red green white yellow but only lasts for a certain time then turns out. i will start documenting the time of appearance an time of doisappearance.

content.detailedDescription:
I stepped out of my back door and noticed 2 reddish lights in eastern sky beyond hills. possibly over orinda or san pablo reservoir. maybe 15 degrees above horizon from our vantage point. one directly above the other. they were stationary then the light on the bottom dropped and disappeared. about 30 seconds later it suddenly reappeared, looking like it suddenly shot upwards. the bottom light then started to move towards the se while the top light remained stationary. the bottom light again reappeared as if it was shot upwards. it continued moving se.  

at this time the top light began to move se as well. both lights dimmed and disappeared.

there were some low clouds in the sky. too distant and too much light interference to capture with our camera. we typically see plane lights in the horizon but these didn't have the blue/red blinking lights we are used to. 

my 8 year old son also partially witnessed the event. the way the light dropped out of the sky and then reappeared is what makes this seem odd.
content.summary: Two flashing lights; one light disappeared with a drop, reappeared suddenly from below, disappeared with drop again, reappeared from below again.

content.detailedDescription:
Myself and an employee were leaving my business in hunters point, located in san francisco, california. as we were about to get into my truck
we both noticed at the same time a bright silver orb that seemed to have a distorted field all around it hovering over san francisco bay.  during our observation ( approx 40 min.)we both seemed to be locked in focus.  the object was spinning fast, directly next to hunters point power station.
it seemed that the object was taking power from the power plant.  the distortion and the inability to remember i had a new top end camera around my head and was unable to use it.  somehow the sphere took hold of our will.  the next thing i remembered was that we had left the city and were in santa clara when we pulled over and said at the same time  " did you see what i saw".  i can't reason why i couldn't take one picture?
has anyone out there seen something like this?
morfeuz60...
content.summary: Two of us observed a silver orb hovering over power station.

content.detailedDescription: I was laying in a hammock by the pool. it was a beautiful day with a few clouds. i was outside for about two hours. i looked up and saw clear as day what looked like a small blue planet sitting next to a cloud. it moved a little sideways in one direction then the other. i took a photograph with my ipad i took a second photo and it was just gone. i would like for someone to see the picture and tell me if anyone rakes has seen anything like it.
content.summary: Saw what looked like a small round planet it was there i took a photo then it was gone

content.detailedDescription: 9/28/13 - 10:23 pm - osprey florida. my wife and i were outside in our spa and we noticed a large cloud like semi transparent vee shaped moving in a straight line at a low altitude. (5-10k ft.)and moving in a steady fast speed.(faster than any aircraft) observed looking south moving from nw to sw direction. sky was mainly clear with some light clouds to our east. no moonlight. very strange! never seen anything like it. no bullshit! would like to discuss this incident with anyone.  we thought perhaps it may be a large bird or a spot light however the object did not move like a bird or a spotlight.
content.summary: Transparent vee shaped object

content.detailedDescription: Myself and three others were driving home from a family members house and when entering rt 130 south in bridgeport,  nj i noticed something odd in the sky.  there were about 8 solid lights in the sky.  there was no apparent shape but they did move very slowly and simultaneously through the sky.  there were some trees that we had to look through so i asked the driver to drive down the road some and pull over.  we saw the lights in the sky with no obstruction and i tried to video tape it with her cell phone but i couldn't focus on them.  we were all in shock of what we were seeing.  there was no way that these were planes or helicopters.  they were silent and too close together.  then they disappeared.  i call my other sister-in-law and told her we just saw a ufo and she laughed at us.  she then looked up on her phone if anyone else has ever reported this before and she found so many sights describing this same event and some had videos.  when i got home i went to the sights she sent us and instantly got the chills when i watched the video from az.  these were the lights we just saw.  i have no doubts about what we just witnessed.  oh and she stopped laughing at me and has been sending me more and more sights about these mysterious lights.  crazy!
content.summary: About 8 round orange lights hoovered in the sky moving slowly and simultaneously for at least 5 minutes the disappeared

content.detailedDescription: On september 28th 2013 at approximately 7:40pm, i was standing in my backyard having a bonfire with my two children, my husband went inside our house to change his clothes after spending the day working on building a deck with a friend. our friend had left but came back when he realized he forgot something, as he walked back into the yard he yelled to me "sarah! look at the sky! do you see that? what is it? as i looked up the "ufo" was right above me, i saw a very round, disk like, object that was moving very slowly,it appeared as though there was fire coming out of the bottom. i called to my husband to come out and see, then the three of us watched for approximately two minutes as it slowly moved across the sky. as we attempted to understand  what we were witnessing at that moment, the best we could come up with was that an airplane one fire, that idea quickly faded when we noticed how slow it was going, the disk like shape, the redness of it, what appeared to be fire and the ominous glow projecting from it as well as the fact that we went inside checked the internet, tv and radio for the next hour to see if we heard anything about it. the object continued on a straight path north west, moving away from all major military bases and airports in the area,very slowly until we lost sight of it. both my husband and i well as our friend were in disbelief at first as we tried to make sense of what we had just witnessed, our first thoughts were to go inside and see if we could find out any information, after doing some research and finding out nothing we have become convinced beyond a doubt that we witnessed a u.F.O. thank-you.
content.summary: A very slow moving disk shaped something seeded to be on fire

content.detailedDescription: Went outside for a cigarette, noticed a orange lit star light / xmas tree ornament style vehicle traveling at 1st west, then it changed to a nw direction and one by one the 5 lights went out on by one ( 4 orange, 1 blight blue ) it made no sound what so ever, left no trail, yet it was apparently on a straight path northwest, it was about 3 miles from my position and was moving slow like a small aircraft , prop driven, i had seen it earlier this week but at about 3:30am and it did the same thing as described here, that time it was moving northeast to south west, i had first thought it was a balloon and the light i was seeing was the gas burner lighting the inner envelope, but tonight's sighting was much clearer and i could see the object much better
content.summary: Straight line, then lights went out 1 by 1

content.detailedDescription: At our rural home in our field.  my son ran in and said come now there are strange lights outside.  there were 3 lights to our left across sky kind of nw triangle blinking in a pattern.  directly north (in front of us) another set of 3 lights triangle blinking in a pattern also.  we looked over to right which would be somewhat east and there was just 1 light.  can't remember if it blinked or not.  none of the lights seemed to move, they were just in same spot.  they blinked on and off kind of in a stair step pattern.  appeared to be either white or maybe kind of amber in color.  there were 3 of us that watched them for about 30 mins.  i got scared so we went in house.  the lights were still there when we went in.  the one to the north in front of us i thought was drifting towards us but i really don't think it was.  i was more scared than anything and probably appeared to be doing that.  that is when i said take me to the house now.  my same son has seen these lights before one time in the climax springs missouri (not far from macks creek area).  we called whiteman air force base and asked if any planes were out and they told us no.  they could have not been flares.  the lights never moved the whole time we watched them.  they stayed in the same spot.  i probably wrong on the date seen, i just can't remember.
content.summary: 3 amber lights triangle blinking in pattern north, 3 lights same to left alittle ways, to right 1 light by itself

content.detailedDescription: On september, 26th i was out for a walk around 00h30 because i couldn't sleep. i was at the top of a hill in the park by my house and i noticed a bright white/red light in the sky that was in the direction of my house. at first i thought nothing of it because i often seen planes and satellites around my area. but when i realized the speed that it was travelling i started to wonder if it could be a ufo. i sat down on some bleachers and just watched the object. it continued in a straight path with an eastward direction; it continued in this path for about a minute. after about a minute it stopped abruptly and started to ascend. it was ascending for about a minute then it vanished. this is not the first time i have seen an object with similar characteristics. two weeks prior to this i saw an object that was similar. it was hovering for a moment, started to ascend and then it vanished. there is one other occasion where i can remember seeing an object like this, i was much younger (around 10 or 11) and i was sitting in my families hottub. in between two trees i saw a light travelling in my direction the it stopped i looked away for just a second and when i redirected my attention back to the area that i saw it, it had vanished.
content.summary: I was walking in the park by my house when i saw a bright red/white light.

content.detailedDescription: I went out on my carport to smoke, and noticed what i thought was a very bright twinkling star, so i watched it for several minutes, and then i saw blue, green, red and sometimes orange lights. i told myself, i've never seen a star do that.  i watched it and it seemed its movement was like wobbling..It never streaked across the sky, it seemed to move very slowly up and down, and side to side...Very small movements, nothing drastic.  i pinpointed my position with a landmark so i could look again the next night to see if i was observing a star, so i called my friend, and she also observed this object and felt like it was something unexplained..I stood on my landmark to see if it had moved, and i noticed it was not located in the same place in the night sky...It had moved further north. this object was in the sky for at least 2 hours.  i tried to video it, but i could not pick it up on my camera. i also woke my husband up, and he observed this strange thing in the sky also....I don't know what it was, but its very exciting to think i may have witnessed something not from our world. i can't wait to check the night sky tonight.
content.summary: It was very bright, twinkled, had blue, red, green, and white lights..It hoovered,

content.detailedDescription: Last night, september 27, 2013, i left my home with a friend, to go get some wine at the grocery store.  as we were leaving the parking lot i noticed up in the sky, directly in front of us, just above the treetops and in the distance over the downtown area, a group of six bright orange starlike objects.  they were grouped close together and appeared to be hovering.  my friend saw them also and i stopped the car while still in the parking lot to watch the lights.  they did not appear to be planes and had no blinking lights on them.  they started moving slowly and heading in our direction.  three of them moved to form a line and the other three stayed grouped together as they started moving closer. my house was very near so i told my friend i would hurry and get my camera as soon as we got to the house.  i looked at the clock in the car and it was 7:54pm and we were looking southeast towards the objects.  i kept an eye on the lights as best as i could while making the less than two minute drive to my house.  i stopped again at one point as one of the lights was going over us.  it was ahead of the others.  it had no navigation lights; was just a steady orange light moving across the sky in a straight line.  i knew i would not have time to get my camera at this point so i pulled into my garage and ran back outside.  i was just in time to see another one of the lights coming.  there was also a small airplane in the distance heading in the opposite direction of the light.  whoever was in that plane had to have seen the orange lights.  then, as it got closer the light started dimming slightly and just as it got directly over my house, it disappeared entirely.  i kept looking, thinking i might see navigation lights, but there was nothing; it was gone.  i waited also for the other lights to come over because i knew there were more, but they never came.  it was a clear night and the stars were out.  i could see no clouds in this part of the sky.  i see a lot of planes where i live and i have never seen anything like this in particular, especially the way they were grouped together and the orange color.  the lack of navigation lights, sound, and the way it just disappeared, was also unlike any plane i have ever seen since i have lived here.  the only thing i felt was that the lights were unusual.
content.summary: Six starlike objects observed grouped together, then started moving

content.detailedDescription:
On the night of september 27, 2013 my wife and i were returning to our home on rauber rd from logan. 
it was about 7:00 pm and was just starting to get dusk. we had just passed nixon rd and my wife looked across the road and said "look at those" she saw six light hovering in a line, when i looked over four of them disappeared and their was two left hovering. they were about 5-6 feet off the ground hovering and pulsating, i could see the tree line behind them and the really strange part was there was a deer and a fox in the field watching them. we witnessed them for about 10 seconds and as we were driving away they both disappeared and the animals ran into the woods.
content.summary: Pulsating lights hovering in field

content.detailedDescription: I was traveling home from work at around 5:00am in the morning and was going down 5mile west of plymouth and suddenly came upon these bright orange circular lights two of them in which had a triangle shape to them side by side hovering and slightly heading nw on 5mile and finally descended past some trees in which i could no longer see them. their lights were flashing in a flashing pattern and i have never ever seen anything like this before. i was so intrigued by the view it had my adrenaline going. i was on my way home at the time and this is a lot of country life area in which i had seen them. it was around 5:30 in the actual time i had viewed this amazing sight.
content.summary: Bright orange light flashing in a circular fashion hovering in which there were two of them and then moved beyond the trees in which i could no longer view them

content.detailedDescription: While coming home with my partner in his brother's car from his father's home in wallsend last night i was in the rear right passenger seat looking out of the window when i observed what appeared to be 3 orbs of blue light flying together in a vertical line pulsating slowly at first i was not sure what i was looking at but when i was able to focus on it's shape it faded out. it could only have been in my view for between 3 and 7 seconds before it was gone. that same evening i saw 2 helicopters heading in that direction.

content.detailedDescription: While walking my dog in bordentown new jersey at 9:33 pm sept. 27, 2013, i witnessed a circular object in the night sky sitting stationary about 1/2 mile beyond the horizon. bright purple lights were seen all around the object then red, blue, back to purple.  this went on for about two minutes then all of a sudden it went completely dark  descending to the ground. i noticed several airplanes above and beyond this object in the night star lit sky.  i could not believe what i was seeing and the extent of vibrant colors this object emitted was extraordinary.
content.summary: Circular object stationary in night sky, went through series of bright purple, red, blue lights then descended into nothing

content.detailedDescription: My brother and i were on our way home. talking about random nonsense. we both looked up at the same time and said nothing until the green yellow and very bright white light shot across the sky at a downward trajectory. when the light stopped we both commented that we were waiting for the impact or some sign of a flash from whatever we saw hitting the ground.It looked as if it was the largest or closest shooting star ever except for the vibrant colors and the extremely large size of the trail.
content.summary: It seemed to be a large firework at first. then realized it was coming down not up.With the naked eye thru the windshield. it was an extremely large shooting star. with very vibrant colors and a very wide trail.

content.detailedDescription: I was looking up and the white lights appeared just like and at the same intensity of the surrounding stars.I noticed them because they were moving slowly across my field of vision rather slowly and i wondered how a plane could move that slow and still be in flight. at first i was like, "what a strange plane because there were no red or green light. what i noticed was a darker field between two star-like lights that was moving slowly across the sky. much slower than a commercial aircraft or satellite. i waited and watched it going across the sky to see if it would blank out some of the stars so i could get a better idea of how big it was. well it was just about to cross over a star field when the darn thing just disappeared into the black. the object moved with a steady rate and did not seem to turn. it was moving gradually across from north to the northeast from my point of view. it was amazing to watch the craft disappear as it appeared as if the white lights of low intensity progressively became smaller, as if they were moving straight up and away from my view. then they either where turned off, or where too far away for me to see them.

content.detailedDescription: It was 11:25 i saw it. i was riding in the backseat of the car looking up at the stars. we were on route 9 in johnsville of bracken county kentucky.I was looking north when i saw it. the best i can describe it, like a green comet but unlike any comet or meteor i've ever seen. it looked to me to be a bright green ball of light that had a halo of white light and two white trails coming off the back. it came from the north and seemed to be falling at an angle of 15 degrees then turned sharply downward. it disappeared behind the trees very quickly. i saw it only for a few seconds. but i think it may have been traveling southeast. if i had held up my thumb the object would have a little bigger. many quarter size. after their object was gone a smoke trail was still visible for a long time. i felt happy and excited to see something so special. but the two others in the car said they felt unsettled.
content.summary: Bright green light
